canonical:
  title: 賀天淸節表
  author: 鄭克永
  language: lzh
  text: 嘉節俯臨慶儀交擧允協三靈之眷胥均萬宇之歡中賀 皇帝赫赫居尊巍巍接統縱橫英偉之略馳號令於風雷出入聖神之機振威靈於遐邇屬虹流之令旦標天與之▣▣百福來同羣蕃允穆臣邈居侯服逖望威顔踊躍歡呼倍百常品
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 賀天淸節表
  author: 鄭克永
  language: lzh
  text: 嘉節俯臨。慶儀交擧。允協三靈之眷。胥均萬宇之歡。中賀。 皇帝赫赫居尊。巍巍接統。縱橫英偉之略。馳號令於風雷。出入聖神之機。振威靈於遐邇。屬虹流之令旦。標天與之▣▣。百福來同。羣蕃允穆。臣邈居侯服。逖望威顔。踊躍歡呼。倍百常品。
korean:
  title: 천청절을 하례하는 표
  author: 정극영
  language: kor
  text: 가절(嘉節)에 임하시어 경전(慶典)을 거행하시니, 진실로 삼령(三靈 하늘ㆍ땅ㆍ사람)의 권애(眷愛)에 맞으며 만방(萬邦)의 즐거움이 고르나이다. 중하(中賀) 황제께서는 혁혁(赫赫)한 지존(至尊)으로서 외외(巍巍)한 황통(皇統)을 이으시니, 종횡으로 영위(英偉)하신 방략(方略)은 바람과 우레같이 호령을 하시고, 나면 성인(聖人), 들면 신(神)이신 기틀은 위령(威靈)이 원근(遠近)에 떨치시나이다. 이제 무지개가 흘러내린 가절(佳節)에 하늘이 주신 □을 표하시니, 온갖 복이 함께 하고 여러 번국(蕃國)이 다 화목하리이다. 신(臣)은 멀리 후복(侯服)에 있사오나 아득히 성안(聖顔)을 바라보고, 용약(踊躍)ㆍ환호함이 보통 때보다 백배나 더합니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0340_010_0420&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Celebrating the Auspicious Day of Heaven's Clarity
  author: Jung Geuk-yeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The auspicious day descends upon us, and ceremonial rites are held in splendor. Truly does this accord with the favor of the Three Spirits—heaven, earth, and humanity—and the joy spreads equally across ten thousand lands.

    In this middle section of praise: The Emperor shines resplendent upon the throne of highest honor, majestic in the succession of imperial power. His strategies, vast and brilliant, issue commands like wind and thunder; his sagely and divine authority radiates its awe-inspiring presence to all corners, near and far. Now, as the rainbow flows down this fine day, Heaven's gift is made manifest. Countless blessings converge, and all tributary nations dwell in harmony.

    Your servant dwells afar in distant lands, yet gazes reverently toward the sacred countenance. In joy and exultation, his heart swells a hundredfold beyond measure.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: The Three Spirits (三靈) represent the cosmic forces of heaven, earth, and humanity in classical East Asian thought.
  - key: ''
    value: This is a formal memorial or petition (表) presented to the emperor on an auspicious occasion, likely the Qingming Festival or similar state celebration.
  - key: ''
    value: The hierarchical structure and formal diction reflect the conventions of official court correspondence during the Joseon period.
